cs.DS, cs.GT, cs.AI, cs.IT, cs.CC. 

The paper deals with a problem in graph theory (finding a large matching in a general graph) and uses algorithms to solve it. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The problem also involves optimization and game theory, which suggests categories such as cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of randomized algorithms and analysis of their performance suggests categories such as cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
